        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Anyway, it matters little what mold the novel of tomorrow will be pulled into. What matters is that the novel should exist, not as a game for murder and not as a pastime for dilettantes or snobs, not as a form of commercial exploitation either, but to answer the need of man to know his fellow man and to know himself. If this is so, and I wish it with all my heart, it will be possible, one day to speak of the era of the novel. ",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
